<h3>What is buildable, what is uncertain</h3>
<p>The LingBot-Video release is genuinely usable: public weights, Diffusers pipeline, SGLang/FP8 serving code, and public benchmark numbers. The main uncertainty is how much the embodiment-aware data mixture and the six reward models actually move physical plausibility, because the reward-model weights and training data are not released.</p>

<p>LingBot-World 2.0 is more visionary but thinner on evidence. The real-time demo requires multi-GPU inference, only the distilled checkpoint is available, and there are no numeric benchmarks. The claim of hour-long stability is impressive if reproducible, but without an evaluation protocol it is hard to verify independently.</p>

