<h3>Limitations</h3>
<p>MIRA is impressive as an engineering demonstration, but it is narrow. The data comes from one bot policy (Nexto), three fixed arenas, and no procedural variation. The paper reports measured stability only to five minutes, with "hours" observed informally. There is no downstream RL validation: no agents are trained inside MIRA and transferred to the real game. And the Action Recoverability Ratio, while useful, is bounded by the codec reconstruction rather than true physical correctness.</p>

